# Segregation of duties (ISO27001 A.5.3): identity-plane changes require
# review from someone outside the requesting team.
#
# CURRENT STATE: this repo has one operator, so the team handles below are
# the intended Phase 2 ownership split, not real GitHub teams today - they
# don't resolve to anyone, and branch protection (configure-repo-protections.py)
# does not set `require_code_owner_reviews`, so this file is not yet an
# enforced gate. It records the intended reviewer-per-area split so wiring
# it up is a config change, not a design decision, once a second
# collaborator exists (see docs/phase2-roadmap.md #5).

/bicep/modules/conditionalAccess.bicep   @your-org/identity-admins
/bicep/modules/pim.bicep                 @your-org/identity-admins
/bicep/modules/rbac/                     @your-org/identity-admins
/bicep/modules/sentinel/                 @your-org/security-ops
/.github/workflows/                      @your-org/platform-admins
